1
00:00:17,616 --> 00:00:21,951
For the past few years,
our rookies haven't performed well.

2
00:00:21,951 --> 00:00:23,779
As a result,

3
00:00:23,779 --> 00:00:29,190
the Dreams have the oldest starting lineup
of all 12 teams.

4
00:00:30,301 --> 00:00:32,777
I am entirely responsible for that outcome.

5
00:00:34,497 --> 00:00:40,251
Who holds the authority
to decide who gets drafted?

6
00:00:41,866 --> 00:00:44,322
Getting right to it, aren't you?

7
00:00:47,779 --> 00:00:52,013
So you plan to investigate our scouting team?

8
00:00:59,761 --> 00:01:03,404
Everyone has two sides to them.

9
00:01:04,511 --> 00:01:08,130
Naive trust is dangerous.

10
00:01:08,130 --> 00:01:09,998
But so is excessive doubt.

11
00:01:12,719 --> 00:01:14,667
Understood.

12
00:01:43,480 --> 00:01:46,440
[High schools]

13
00:02:00,291 --> 00:02:03,560
I see we've selected rather obscure players.

14
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:06,296
Sorry? I'm not following.

15
00:02:06,296 --> 00:02:08,448
Yeah! We have specialists who...

16
00:02:08,448 --> 00:02:10,508
You two, settle down.

17
00:02:10,508 --> 00:02:16,077
GM, our reliable scouts nationwide
have gathered this intel for us.

18
00:02:16,077 --> 00:02:19,112
Yes, our colleagues work tirelessly to...

19
00:02:19,112 --> 00:02:23,969
Why was our first draft pick in 2020
an obscure player,

20
00:02:23,969 --> 00:02:27,714
when the baseball Koshien that year
was canceled due to COVID?

21
00:02:29,281 --> 00:02:32,297
Our picks for rookies have suffered since.

22
00:02:32,935 --> 00:02:34,955
Luck is a part of the draft.

23
00:02:34,955 --> 00:02:36,661
Yes, luck plays a major role.

24
00:02:36,661 --> 00:02:38,805
- That's enough.
- But sir!

25
00:02:38,805 --> 00:02:40,014
Then I'll show him.

26
00:02:40,014 --> 00:02:42,478
Stop, you're no better.

27
00:02:42,478 --> 00:02:44,014
What's that supposed to mean?

28
00:02:44,014 --> 00:02:46,538
Have we been unlucky for six years straight?

29
00:02:46,538 --> 00:02:50,410
I believe that may not entirely be the case.

30
00:02:50,410 --> 00:02:51,938
Hold on a minute.

31
00:02:51,938 --> 00:02:53,150
Kikuchi, stop it.

32
00:02:53,150 --> 00:02:56,410
I can't sit, and let him run his mouth, sir.

33
00:02:56,410 --> 00:02:58,950
Just let me say this.

34
00:03:01,817 --> 00:03:06,495
Mr. Kurokawa is not at fault.

35
00:03:09,369 --> 00:03:12,706
Mr. Kurokawa, why aren't you
standing up for yourself?

36
00:03:12,706 --> 00:03:18,011
We were trying to draft Yuma Arihara.

37
00:03:18,011 --> 00:03:20,062
Arihara...

38
00:03:20,062 --> 00:03:22,438
- The Vikings' shortstop, right?
- That's right.

39
00:03:22,438 --> 00:03:23,784
But then?

40
00:03:23,784 --> 00:03:29,991
Osanai, one of our amateur scouts
at the time,

41
00:03:29,991 --> 00:03:33,753
insisted on drafting Satozaki
from Gifu Daini.

42
00:03:35,078 --> 00:03:37,738
No, in the end, I also agreed to it.

43
00:03:37,738 --> 00:03:39,724
That wasn't Osanai's fault.

44
00:03:39,724 --> 00:03:41,058
No, no, no, no, no.

45
00:03:41,058 --> 00:03:42,709
This Osanai.

46
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:44,640
Where is he now?

47
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:45,753
Beats me.

48
00:03:45,753 --> 00:03:50,535
Scouts are supposed to be team players,
darn it.

49
00:03:50,535 --> 00:03:54,045
Osanai! Where'd you go?

50
00:03:54,045 --> 00:03:56,827
Our GM's looking for you, Osanai.

51
00:03:56,827 --> 00:03:58,488
Quit grandstanding!

52
00:03:58,488 --> 00:04:00,194
Show yourself already, Osanai!

53
00:04:00,194 --> 00:04:03,128
We're getting impatient, you rascal.

54
00:04:03,128 --> 00:04:05,704
It's my fault I can't wrangle
my own subordinates.

55
00:04:05,704 --> 00:04:08,489
No, no. You're not at fault, sir.

56
00:04:08,489 --> 00:04:10,691
Don't come and defend me.

57
00:04:10,691 --> 00:04:14,353
You're only making things awkward.
It's counterproductive.

58
00:04:14,353 --> 00:04:18,459
Oh, geez! My apologies! I spoke out of line.

59
00:04:18,459 --> 00:04:19,834
The floor is yours.

60
00:04:19,834 --> 00:04:22,611
Let's revisit this matter another day.

61
00:04:22,611 --> 00:04:26,000
Understood. I will go see Osanai myself.

62
00:04:28,075 --> 00:04:30,953
If there's any wrongdoing, I'll be fired.

63
00:04:30,953 --> 00:04:34,272
If there's any wrongdoing, you will be.

64
00:04:36,363 --> 00:04:37,964
GM!

65
00:04:40,510 --> 00:04:42,896
Why were you badgering him?

66
00:04:42,896 --> 00:04:44,554
Who?

67
00:04:44,554 --> 00:04:46,690
Mr. Kurokawa.

68
00:04:46,690 --> 00:04:48,558
The 2020 draft was six years ago.

69
00:04:48,558 --> 00:04:52,119
Why are you pursuing accountability, now?

70
00:04:52,119 --> 00:04:53,647
Why not?

71
00:04:53,647 --> 00:04:57,041
The 2020 draft
was not under your jurisdiction.

72
00:04:57,041 --> 00:05:00,639
It is so we do not repeat our mistakes.

73
00:05:00,639 --> 00:05:03,151
I commend you for bringing back Sawada.

74
00:05:03,151 --> 00:05:04,986
- President Makita.
- Yes?

75
00:05:05,821 --> 00:05:08,683
Do you trust our Scouting Director,
Mr. Kurokawa?

76
00:05:08,683 --> 00:05:11,921
Of course I do. We've been
working together for years now.

77
00:05:11,921 --> 00:05:14,646
- Is that your only reason?
- Huh?

78
00:05:15,638 --> 00:05:18,126
Your trust is baseless.

79
00:05:18,126 --> 00:05:20,376
You've confirmed nothing for yourself.

80
00:05:21,490 --> 00:05:24,627
You're speaking so coldly again.

81
00:05:24,627 --> 00:05:26,455
We've been through thick and thin together.

82
00:05:26,455 --> 00:05:30,136
Then you're satisfied with uncertainty.

83
00:05:30,136 --> 00:05:33,244
GM, wouldn't you be hurt if we doubted you?

84
00:05:35,064 --> 00:05:37,393
Doesn't seem like it.

85
00:05:38,455 --> 00:05:40,906
I'd rather work with someone who doubts me,

86
00:05:40,906 --> 00:05:43,421
than an observer who only knows trust.

87
00:05:43,421 --> 00:05:46,874
Where does that steel-like confidence
of yours come from?

88
00:06:24,142 --> 00:06:25,448
Shift's over!

89
00:06:25,448 --> 00:06:28,717
Alright everyone,
it's welcome party time!

90
00:06:28,717 --> 00:06:30,261
Party!

91
00:06:30,261 --> 00:06:31,957
That's right, party!

92
00:06:31,957 --> 00:06:33,987
The night is still young! Party!

93
00:06:33,987 --> 00:06:36,467
Could you not start weird chants?

94
00:06:36,467 --> 00:06:38,223
Just get ready already.

95
00:06:38,223 --> 00:06:39,794
But, Prez.

96
00:06:39,794 --> 00:06:43,277
Coaches and staff
rarely grab drinks together!

97
00:06:43,277 --> 00:06:44,431
Right, Mr. Kurokawa?

98
00:06:44,431 --> 00:06:46,038
He's right.

99
00:06:47,071 --> 00:06:48,259
Where's the GM?

100
00:06:48,259 --> 00:06:50,385
He's meeting us there.

101
00:06:50,385 --> 00:06:52,104
Yikes, let's go.

102
00:06:52,104 --> 00:06:54,404
Huh? Wait a minute! Wait up!

103
00:06:55,692 --> 00:06:57,382
Long hallway, eh?

104
00:06:58,482 --> 00:07:00,315
Everyone, please take off your slippers.

105
00:07:00,315 --> 00:07:01,472
- We know.
- Okay!

106
00:07:01,472 --> 00:07:03,243
- It's a tatami room.
- Right.

107
00:07:03,243 --> 00:07:05,062
- Welcome.
- Who wouldn't take off their slippers?

108
00:07:05,062 --> 00:07:06,571
Careful, there's a step here.

109
00:07:06,571 --> 00:07:08,198
Guess he's not here yet.

110
00:07:08,198 --> 00:07:10,024
- Try contacting him.
- Yes, ma'am.

111
00:07:10,024 --> 00:07:11,611
That won't be necessary.

112
00:07:11,611 --> 00:07:13,966
- Whoa!
- You were early?

113
00:07:13,966 --> 00:07:16,156
We were scheduled for 7PM, no?

114
00:07:19,138 --> 00:07:21,313
- Yikes.
- We're so sorry.

115
00:07:21,313 --> 00:07:23,230
We're late because of your stupid chant.

116
00:07:23,230 --> 00:07:25,098
No, it was because you were slow!

117
00:07:25,098 --> 00:07:26,135
It was your fault!

118
00:07:26,135 --> 00:07:27,423
- It was yours!
- No, yours!

119
00:07:27,423 --> 00:07:29,549
Please, let me enjoy my drinks
in peace tonight!

120
00:07:29,549 --> 00:07:31,341
Quit it with the lover's quarrel.

121
00:07:31,341 --> 00:07:34,101
Look, see? You two are holding up the line.

122
00:07:34,101 --> 00:07:36,427
- We're so sorry.
- Real sorry, folks.

123
00:07:36,427 --> 00:07:38,152
- Guide them in.
- Right this way.

124
00:07:55,719 --> 00:07:56,968
Testing, testing.

125
00:07:56,968 --> 00:08:00,416
Alright everyone, your attention, please.

126
00:08:00,416 --> 00:08:04,168
I'd like to invite the GM up
to give a few words.

127
00:08:04,168 --> 00:08:06,380
GM, if you'd please.

128
00:08:06,380 --> 00:08:08,474
Let's hear it for the GM!

129
00:08:09,381 --> 00:08:11,752
That's our GM!

130
00:08:20,768 --> 00:08:24,693
Again, I am Sakurazaki, the GM.

131
00:08:26,858 --> 00:08:30,093
I fully respect your ways
and method of operations.

132
00:08:31,992 --> 00:08:35,392
However, I believe change is necessary.

133
00:08:36,604 --> 00:08:40,685
I acquired Sawada in place of Kudo.

134
00:08:40,685 --> 00:08:43,380
I will do whatever is necessary for the team.

135
00:08:43,380 --> 00:08:47,866
I will not hesitate to cut off anything,
or anyone, who causes the team harm.

136
00:08:54,066 --> 00:08:56,088
Here's to our success, as a team.

137
00:08:59,376 --> 00:09:01,594
Give it up for our GM!

138
00:09:03,663 --> 00:09:06,448
Thank you GM, for the riveting greeting.

139
00:09:10,471 --> 00:09:11,850
Yes! That's our GM!

140
00:09:11,850 --> 00:09:14,749
Sounded more like a declaration of war to me.

141
00:09:14,749 --> 00:09:19,734
Yes. He's putting
quite a bit of pressure on us.

142
00:09:19,734 --> 00:09:21,632
How annoying.

143
00:09:33,456 --> 00:09:36,554
Hey, are you really okay with that?

144
00:09:36,554 --> 00:09:38,750
Mr. Kurokawa, he's approaching.

145
00:09:38,750 --> 00:09:40,305
Sure, Mom.

146
00:09:40,305 --> 00:09:41,620
I'll call you back.

147
00:09:41,620 --> 00:09:43,844
Yeah. Take care.

148
00:09:44,537 --> 00:09:45,777
Are you alright, Mr. Kurokawa?

149
00:09:45,777 --> 00:09:47,631
Someone, help! His knee!

150
00:09:47,631 --> 00:09:49,234
- I think he broke something!
- No, no.

151
00:09:49,234 --> 00:09:52,149
Quit exaggerating, I'm fine.

152
00:09:52,149 --> 00:09:56,053
And he has me locked on.

153
00:09:56,053 --> 00:09:57,747
Sir, leave this to me.

154
00:09:58,762 --> 00:10:01,729
Was there something you needed?

155
00:10:02,784 --> 00:10:05,853
Right, I thought so. I kept the seat warm.
Here, it's all yours.

156
00:10:09,938 --> 00:10:12,097
Here, have a drink.

157
00:10:12,744 --> 00:10:14,028
Thank you.

158
00:10:19,669 --> 00:10:22,434
Now that trade.

159
00:10:22,434 --> 00:10:24,985
That was just brilliant.

160
00:10:30,071 --> 00:10:33,013
Do you have any requests for me?

161
00:10:33,013 --> 00:10:34,494
Requests, eh?

162
00:10:35,630 --> 00:10:37,866
Hold a drinking party every month.

163
00:10:37,866 --> 00:10:40,493
Nice one, Mr. Kurokawa.

164
00:10:40,493 --> 00:10:42,392
Since Toyohashi is famous for its chikuwa,

165
00:10:42,392 --> 00:10:44,212
I suggest we get oden every month.

166
00:10:44,212 --> 00:10:45,446
We could go bar hopping.

167
00:10:45,446 --> 00:10:48,011
A foodie tour doesn't sound bad at all.

168
00:10:52,354 --> 00:10:54,086
I'm just kidding.

169
00:10:54,086 --> 00:10:56,773
You asked for requests, was it? Let's see...

170
00:10:56,773 --> 00:10:58,887
Ah, I do have one.

171
00:10:58,887 --> 00:11:02,314
Pro scouts cover 12 teams
and independent leagues.

172
00:11:02,314 --> 00:11:05,476
Amateurs cover middle school
to university leagues.

173
00:11:05,476 --> 00:11:08,313
Our job is to observe the play styles

174
00:11:08,313 --> 00:11:11,963
and personalities of promising players.

175
00:11:11,963 --> 00:11:13,853
- That's right.
- Idiot!

176
00:11:13,853 --> 00:11:15,236
You're very dedicated to your work.

177
00:11:15,236 --> 00:11:17,288
You didn't need to get involved...

178
00:11:17,288 --> 00:11:20,947
When a scout is fired or transferred,

179
00:11:20,947 --> 00:11:25,219
it's a rule to hand over
all their materials to their successor.

180
00:11:25,219 --> 00:11:27,624
We love clear-cut rules!

181
00:11:27,624 --> 00:11:28,745
Absolutely!

182
00:11:28,745 --> 00:11:33,857
But the instincts I've developed
can't be passed on.

183
00:11:33,857 --> 00:11:36,216
I see.

184
00:11:36,216 --> 00:11:39,956
So you're saying personnel changes
are unnecessary for scouts.

185
00:11:41,432 --> 00:11:44,479
Well, that's one way to put it.

186
00:11:45,369 --> 00:11:49,194
I'll carefully consider
if those words were advice...

187
00:11:49,855 --> 00:11:52,454
or an attempt at abusing your authority.

188
00:11:52,454 --> 00:11:54,019
GM.

189
00:11:54,019 --> 00:11:56,385
Isn't that going too far?

190
00:11:58,533 --> 00:12:02,021
Now, now, let's lighten up and have a drink!

191
00:12:02,021 --> 00:12:03,029
Anyone wants tequila?

192
00:12:03,029 --> 00:12:04,917
- Just come back.
- Ow, ow, ow!

193
00:12:04,917 --> 00:12:07,371
Yes, I understand! I'm sorry.

194
00:12:08,933 --> 00:12:11,551
- Hey!
- Please, just not the suspenders.

195
00:12:11,551 --> 00:12:14,875
Evening, folks. What a party this is.

196
00:12:14,875 --> 00:12:17,298
Please, there's no need.

197
00:12:17,298 --> 00:12:19,571
Relax.

198
00:12:21,175 --> 00:12:22,824
Oh?

199
00:12:22,824 --> 00:12:25,098
Was I interrupting?

200
00:12:25,098 --> 00:12:26,953
No, no, of course not!

201
00:12:26,953 --> 00:12:28,782
Your presence is more than welcome, sir.

202
00:12:28,782 --> 00:12:31,407
I'll get you both a plate and chopsticks.

203
00:12:31,407 --> 00:12:33,564
I'm fine, thank you.

204
00:12:33,564 --> 00:12:35,731
I only came to settle the bill,

205
00:12:35,731 --> 00:12:38,994
but I simply had to join in the fun.

206
00:12:39,975 --> 00:12:43,087
May I sit right over here?

207
00:12:43,087 --> 00:12:44,059
Sir, if you'd like--

208
00:12:44,059 --> 00:12:45,718
Watch out!

209
00:12:45,718 --> 00:12:47,574
I'm terribly sorry.

210
00:12:47,574 --> 00:12:49,836
- Please, go ahead.
- Move it!

211
00:12:50,869 --> 00:12:53,225
Pardon my interruption.

212
00:12:58,776 --> 00:13:03,636
Mr. Kurokawa is a very responsible person.

213
00:13:03,636 --> 00:13:07,651
When he was an active player,
I was actually a fan.

214
00:13:07,651 --> 00:13:09,383
I'm honored, sir.

215
00:13:10,806 --> 00:13:15,151
A decorated athlete,
who is now Scouting Director.

216
00:13:15,151 --> 00:13:17,391
There is a slight disjoint there, no?

217
00:13:17,391 --> 00:13:20,521
I often think that myself.

218
00:13:20,521 --> 00:13:22,233
- There he goes
- Kurokawa's history,

219
00:13:22,233 --> 00:13:24,311
and his title of Scouting Director.

220
00:13:24,311 --> 00:13:26,343
They are slightly disjointed.

221
00:13:26,343 --> 00:13:29,093
My words exactly.

222
00:13:29,093 --> 00:13:32,055
Now would you please can it?

223
00:13:32,833 --> 00:13:36,026
As you wish, sir!

224
00:13:36,026 --> 00:13:40,881
I offered him the position of manager.

225
00:13:44,173 --> 00:13:49,065
However, he insisted his role
as Scouting Director was crucial,

226
00:13:49,065 --> 00:13:51,280
and shot me clean down.

227
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:55,237
A truly moving story, is that not?

228
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:03,208
I think I'll have a drink.

229
00:14:03,208 --> 00:14:05,729
- Come, bring him a cold one.
- Oh, it's fine.

230
00:14:05,729 --> 00:14:07,966
- Miyahara, please.
- Beer!

231
00:14:13,288 --> 00:14:17,532
Well then, I bid you all a good night.

232
00:14:17,532 --> 00:14:19,253
May I ask one question?

233
00:14:22,977 --> 00:14:25,639
The manager was here with us today.

234
00:14:25,639 --> 00:14:27,711
What about it?

235
00:14:28,753 --> 00:14:35,134
He may have overheard your offer to Kurokawa.

236
00:14:42,184 --> 00:14:44,035
Is that so?

237
00:14:44,035 --> 00:14:45,921
I understand.

238
00:14:48,615 --> 00:14:51,443
How could you say that to the President!

239
00:14:51,443 --> 00:14:53,064
I thought he ought to know.

240
00:14:53,064 --> 00:14:56,823
Must be nice, being able to speak your mind.

241
00:15:09,722 --> 00:15:10,971
Prez.

242
00:15:10,971 --> 00:15:13,183
My heart just clenched.

243
00:15:13,183 --> 00:15:14,674
Yeah.

244
00:15:26,621 --> 00:15:29,490
I brushed it aside earlier,

245
00:15:29,490 --> 00:15:33,068
but I can't help but think back to it.

246
00:15:34,855 --> 00:15:39,328
Was the GM lecturing me?

247
00:15:39,328 --> 00:15:43,550
No, no. For a mere GM to lecture you?
Unthinkable.

248
00:15:43,550 --> 00:15:46,478
What kind of person is he?

249
00:15:46,478 --> 00:15:48,608
Erm...

250
00:15:49,872 --> 00:15:52,305
What do you mean by that, sir?

251
00:15:52,305 --> 00:15:54,974
I'm asking if he will obey me.

252
00:15:55,695 --> 00:15:57,467
That is, well...

253
00:15:57,467 --> 00:15:59,812
Some individuals hold no power,

254
00:15:59,812 --> 00:16:02,545
yet they have conviction.

255
00:16:02,545 --> 00:16:06,087
I find these sorts of individuals...

256
00:16:06,087 --> 00:16:08,653
to be absolutely detestable.

257
00:16:10,312 --> 00:16:16,552
The conviction these people hold
can, and will be broken.

258
00:16:17,294 --> 00:16:20,649
I cannot wait to see it happen.

259
00:16:36,857 --> 00:16:38,768
<i>Today,</i>

260
00:16:38,768 --> 00:16:43,189
<i>I'll be reuniting with a teacher
who I haven't seen since graduating.</i>

261
00:16:43,189 --> 00:16:45,771
- I'm home!
- Oh, welcome back.

262
00:16:45,771 --> 00:16:50,167
Your adorable, exhausted sister is back.

263
00:16:50,167 --> 00:16:52,202
- Where's dinner?
- I didn't cook.

264
00:16:52,202 --> 00:16:54,608
Just be quiet for a moment.
This is where it gets good.

265
00:16:54,608 --> 00:16:57,064
You're not working, so at least make dinner.

266
00:16:57,064 --> 00:16:58,417
I'm looking for work.

267
00:16:58,417 --> 00:17:03,537
I want a job where I can maximize my charm.

268
00:17:03,537 --> 00:17:04,612
I've heard that before.

269
00:17:04,612 --> 00:17:06,268
Please, just be quiet for a moment.

270
00:17:06,268 --> 00:17:07,505
See, watch.

271
00:17:07,505 --> 00:17:09,652
- She's reuniting with her mentor.
- <i>Mrs. Tanaka!</i>

272
00:17:09,652 --> 00:17:11,205
- See? See?
- <i>Long time no see.</i>

273
00:17:11,205 --> 00:17:12,778
- <i>How have you been?</i>
- <i>I've been doing well.</i>

274
00:17:12,778 --> 00:17:14,547
<i>I'm so happy to see you!</i>

275
00:17:14,547 --> 00:17:17,804
Oh, no!

276
00:17:18,901 --> 00:17:21,727
Do you remember Mr. Yamashita
from junior high?

277
00:17:21,727 --> 00:17:23,683
Oh, I remember him. Why?

278
00:17:23,683 --> 00:17:27,582
He was my favorite teacher.

279
00:17:27,582 --> 00:17:29,190
Huh? Why?

280
00:17:29,190 --> 00:17:30,987
- I was always playing around, right?
- Yeah.

281
00:17:30,987 --> 00:17:32,607
Well, Mr. Yamashita set me straight.

282
00:17:32,607 --> 00:17:35,665
He said, "you're underestimating yourself".

283
00:17:35,665 --> 00:17:40,263
So then you changed your ways
and studied diligently?

284
00:17:40,263 --> 00:17:41,431
Yup.

285
00:17:43,954 --> 00:17:46,961
Hey. How was that funny?

286
00:17:46,961 --> 00:17:48,992
Well, here's the thing.

287
00:17:48,992 --> 00:17:52,869
Mom actually asked the teacher
to encourage you.

288
00:17:52,869 --> 00:17:54,090
What?

289
00:17:54,809 --> 00:17:56,329
- Seriously?
- Dead serious.

290
00:17:56,329 --> 00:17:57,691
Why?

291
00:17:57,691 --> 00:18:00,373
To give you the motivation you needed.

292
00:18:00,373 --> 00:18:02,893
For real?

293
00:18:02,893 --> 00:18:05,490
My respect for Mr. Yamashita just shattered.

294
00:18:05,490 --> 00:18:08,712
Really? I highly doubt it.

295
00:18:08,712 --> 00:18:10,358
I didn't want to hear that secret.

296
00:18:10,358 --> 00:18:13,358
Oh, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

297
00:18:13,358 --> 00:18:18,582
<i>Ms. Tanaka, I greatly treasure
your presence in my life.</i>

298
00:18:30,377 --> 00:18:33,813
<i>He insisted his role
as Scouting Director was crucial,</i>

299
00:18:33,813 --> 00:18:35,602
<i>and shot me clean down.</i>

300
00:18:35,602 --> 00:18:37,804
<i>Your trust is baseless.</i>

301
00:18:37,804 --> 00:18:40,574
<i>You've confirmed nothing for yourself.</i>

302
00:18:50,725 --> 00:18:52,167
You're still here?

303
00:18:52,167 --> 00:18:54,053
- I'm working overtime.
- Are you done?

304
00:18:54,053 --> 00:18:55,780
Now I am!

305
00:18:55,780 --> 00:18:58,777
Okay, then make a list of players drafted

306
00:18:58,777 --> 00:19:02,036
in the last six years,
grouped by their high school.

307
00:19:02,036 --> 00:19:07,428
I, Itsuki Miyahara,
hear your request loud and clear, ma'am.

308
00:19:07,428 --> 00:19:09,418
Why are you being so dramatic?

309
00:19:09,418 --> 00:19:11,962
I'm happy you rely on me.

310
00:19:11,962 --> 00:19:14,443
I'm not relying on you,
I'm giving you an order.

311
00:19:14,443 --> 00:19:16,325
Oh, come on.

312
00:19:16,325 --> 00:19:18,025
Just do it already.

313
00:19:18,025 --> 00:19:19,775
[List of drafts by school, 2020-2025]

314
00:19:21,392 --> 00:19:23,186
And sent!

315
00:19:23,186 --> 00:19:25,025
Thank you.

316
00:19:26,479 --> 00:19:28,342
That's it?

317
00:19:28,342 --> 00:19:31,077
No hugs for your capable junior?

318
00:19:31,077 --> 00:19:33,151
- No pushing him against a wall?
- Hey.

319
00:19:33,151 --> 00:19:34,993
No pulling down my suspenders with a snap?

320
00:19:34,993 --> 00:19:37,028
Be quiet.

321
00:19:38,419 --> 00:19:40,032
What's wrong?

322
00:19:44,060 --> 00:19:48,160
[Scouting Director]

323
00:19:54,617 --> 00:19:56,625
What are you doing?

324
00:19:56,625 --> 00:19:58,824
- Be quiet.
- Huh?

325
00:20:00,125 --> 00:20:01,316
You're still around?

326
00:20:01,316 --> 00:20:02,878
Good evening.

327
00:20:02,878 --> 00:20:04,442
We're working overtime...

328
00:20:04,442 --> 00:20:07,719
I see. Good work.

329
00:20:12,398 --> 00:20:14,734
- I'll get that.
- Sure.

330
00:20:14,734 --> 00:20:16,435
Yes, hello?

331
00:20:18,463 --> 00:20:20,568
What? The police?

332
00:20:20,568 --> 00:20:21,949
Huh?

333
00:20:23,847 --> 00:20:26,111
Tanigaki got into a fight.

334
00:20:30,164 --> 00:20:33,232
That was close, wasn't it?

335
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:36,678
Even if someone insults the Dreams,
fighting is not allowed.

336
00:20:36,678 --> 00:20:38,853
Please be very careful.

337
00:20:38,853 --> 00:20:40,642
I apologize.

338
00:20:40,642 --> 00:20:43,124
If you do the same thing again, you're fired.

339
00:20:43,124 --> 00:20:44,609
Yes, ma'am.

340
00:20:44,609 --> 00:20:46,649
You should be careful.

341
00:20:46,649 --> 00:20:49,202
When Prez gets angry,
she turns into a real demon.

342
00:20:49,202 --> 00:20:51,253
- Don't say anything unnecessary!
- Ow! That hurts!

343
00:20:51,253 --> 00:20:53,143
- Back to the office we go.
- Ma'am, please!

344
00:20:53,143 --> 00:20:55,910
- Not in front of the police station!
- Pipe down.

345
00:20:55,910 --> 00:20:57,278
Hey.

346
00:20:58,899 --> 00:21:01,037
How are your parents?

347
00:21:02,371 --> 00:21:03,900
They're fine.

348
00:21:03,900 --> 00:21:06,193
Give them my regards.

349
00:21:20,846 --> 00:21:24,464
You know the players' parents?

350
00:21:24,464 --> 00:21:25,971
Yeah.

351
00:21:26,864 --> 00:21:28,766
Even if a player's short,

352
00:21:28,766 --> 00:21:34,629
they could hit a growth spurt
if their parents are tall, you know?

353
00:21:35,727 --> 00:21:40,903
When scouting players,
what do you prioritize most?

354
00:21:40,903 --> 00:21:43,597
- That's gotta be...
- I wasn't asking you.

355
00:21:43,597 --> 00:21:45,264
Physicality is number one.

356
00:21:45,264 --> 00:21:47,380
Right, I thought so!

357
00:21:47,380 --> 00:21:49,526
If there are no issues there,

358
00:21:49,526 --> 00:21:54,029
then it's all about character and motivation.

359
00:21:54,029 --> 00:21:56,534
That's our Scouting Director!

360
00:21:57,717 --> 00:21:59,460
I see...

361
00:22:01,141 --> 00:22:07,216
But, Tanigaki, the rehabilitating Okajima,

362
00:22:07,216 --> 00:22:12,217
and the now retired, unsuccessful Kurata
were all physically weak.

363
00:22:14,528 --> 00:22:16,695
Prez?

364
00:22:16,695 --> 00:22:19,750
I trust your eye, Mr. Kurokawa.

365
00:22:20,459 --> 00:22:25,340
But there are some players
I simply don't know why you chose.

366
00:22:25,340 --> 00:22:28,300
I understand scouting can come
with certain temptations, as well.

367
00:22:28,300 --> 00:22:29,856
Makita.

368
00:22:31,408 --> 00:22:33,247
Yes.

369
00:22:33,247 --> 00:22:35,448
What do you think you're doing?

370
00:22:38,651 --> 00:22:41,351
I admit, I'm incompetent.

371
00:22:42,129 --> 00:22:44,724
But I won't tolerate being suspected.

372
00:22:45,931 --> 00:22:47,860
Stop the car.

373
00:22:51,782 --> 00:22:55,170
Is it just me,
or does it feel stuffy in here?

374
00:22:55,170 --> 00:22:56,312
Hey, I know.

375
00:22:56,312 --> 00:23:00,880
Why don't we all sing the Dreams' team song?

376
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:02,151
Let's sing! Come on!

377
00:23:02,151 --> 00:23:03,931
After me, folks!

378
00:23:10,435 --> 00:23:11,761
Okay!

379
00:23:11,761 --> 00:23:12,993
Go!

380
00:23:15,281 --> 00:23:17,595
Great!

381
00:23:19,957 --> 00:23:21,012
Nice, nice!

382
00:23:21,012 --> 00:23:23,086
Nice catch!

383
00:23:23,086 --> 00:23:24,628
Alright, he's getting in the groove.

384
00:23:24,628 --> 00:23:26,751
- How's this?
- Looking good.

385
00:23:29,357 --> 00:23:30,987
Who are you?

386
00:23:32,364 --> 00:23:34,413
What is that?

387
00:23:34,413 --> 00:23:35,951
Well...

388
00:23:38,110 --> 00:23:40,028
Were you passing through the neighborhood?

389
00:23:41,904 --> 00:23:44,225
Yes, something like that.

390
00:23:48,610 --> 00:23:50,715
Are you knowledgeable about baseball?

391
00:23:51,352 --> 00:23:54,882
No. Not really.

392
00:23:57,254 --> 00:24:00,783
Do you know how many seconds it takes
to run from home to first?

393
00:24:02,034 --> 00:24:04,269
About six seconds?

394
00:24:05,230 --> 00:24:07,142
For a right-handed batter, 4.3 seconds.

395
00:24:07,142 --> 00:24:09,804
For a left-handed batter, 4.0 seconds.

396
00:24:09,804 --> 00:24:13,039
That's enough to tell you
which kids will go pro.

397
00:24:13,039 --> 00:24:14,990
Know why?

398
00:24:16,675 --> 00:24:18,577
Because they're fast?

399
00:24:19,224 --> 00:24:22,722
Well, it's partly because they're athletic.

400
00:24:22,722 --> 00:24:27,085
But kids who sprint to first
always succeed as pros.

401
00:24:28,266 --> 00:24:30,380
Because they're the real hard workers.

402
00:24:32,605 --> 00:24:35,091
Alright! You guys got this!

403
00:24:41,539 --> 00:24:43,414
He's losing his grip strength.

404
00:24:44,489 --> 00:24:46,229
Change the pitcher.

405
00:24:51,329 --> 00:24:53,303
You can't keep him in.

406
00:24:53,303 --> 00:24:54,433
He'll injure his shoulder!

407
00:24:54,433 --> 00:24:55,665
I know, I understand.

408
00:24:55,665 --> 00:24:56,677
- You clearly don't.
- Let's calm down.

409
00:24:56,677 --> 00:24:57,966
I mean, aren't you the manager here?

410
00:24:57,966 --> 00:24:58,973
We have our reasons.

411
00:24:58,973 --> 00:25:00,626
A player's career is on the line!

412
00:25:00,626 --> 00:25:01,493
Let's calm down.

413
00:25:01,493 --> 00:25:03,311
- Protect the player!
- Now, now.

414
00:25:04,765 --> 00:25:07,362
- Sir, here.
- It's no big deal.

415
00:25:07,362 --> 00:25:10,171
Thank you very much. You really helped me.

416
00:25:10,171 --> 00:25:12,216
I'm so grateful it went well.

417
00:25:12,216 --> 00:25:13,420
- Heading back?
- Yes.

418
00:25:13,420 --> 00:25:14,551
- Keep it up.
- I will.

419
00:25:14,551 --> 00:25:15,635
Thank you.

420
00:25:15,635 --> 00:25:17,390
Take care, sir.

421
00:25:20,556 --> 00:25:22,375
Good work.

422
00:25:22,375 --> 00:25:24,501
Wait, you're still here?

423
00:25:24,501 --> 00:25:26,533
Who exactly are you?

424
00:25:28,088 --> 00:25:31,674
I'm the GM of the Dreams. Sakurazaki.

425
00:25:31,674 --> 00:25:33,385
I called you yesterday.

426
00:25:33,385 --> 00:25:35,712
Huh? Our GM? Seriously?

427
00:25:36,753 --> 00:25:40,012
- Yes.
- You should have said so.

428
00:25:42,870 --> 00:25:44,569
Oh, no, please don't get the wrong idea.

429
00:25:44,569 --> 00:25:47,422
This isn't a bribe or anything.

430
00:25:51,462 --> 00:25:53,646
May I see it?

431
00:25:55,226 --> 00:25:56,591
Yes.

432
00:26:25,385 --> 00:26:26,593
[Draft News]

433
00:26:26,593 --> 00:26:30,333
[Mystery of the First Round Tanigaki Pick]

434
00:26:32,860 --> 00:26:35,520
[Bribing the scouts?]

435
00:26:42,572 --> 00:26:44,639
<i>How are your parents?</i>

436
00:26:45,481 --> 00:26:46,609
<i>They're fine.</i>

437
00:26:46,609 --> 00:26:51,009
<i>Mom asked the teacher to encourage you.</i>

438
00:27:09,334 --> 00:27:10,916
Even though it's the off-season,

439
00:27:10,916 --> 00:27:12,954
you're always practicing until it's late.

440
00:27:14,891 --> 00:27:16,710
I have to make up for what I'm lacking.

441
00:27:16,710 --> 00:27:21,207
A player chosen first in the draft
couldn't be "lacking".

442
00:27:29,110 --> 00:27:31,661
The Draft Lottery is coming up again.

443
00:27:35,722 --> 00:27:38,626
Bad rumors about you are spreading.

444
00:27:43,188 --> 00:27:45,149
Tanigaki.

445
00:27:48,093 --> 00:27:51,548
How much did you give Mr. Kurokawa?

446
00:27:58,267 --> 00:28:01,161
I only know about baseball.
Anything else is...

447
00:28:01,161 --> 00:28:03,603
Please, tell me the truth.

448
00:28:03,603 --> 00:28:06,079
I won't cause you any trouble.

449
00:28:09,787 --> 00:28:13,219
You're already causing me enough trouble.

450
00:28:13,219 --> 00:28:15,078
Please leave!

451
00:28:41,071 --> 00:28:43,004
Are you prepared?

452
00:28:48,390 --> 00:28:50,791
If I tell you everything,

453
00:28:50,791 --> 00:28:55,618
both my career and Mr. Kurokawa's
will be put in jeopardy.

454
00:28:56,933 --> 00:28:59,166
Can you be held responsible for that?

455
00:29:05,826 --> 00:29:10,482
I had lent him money
to get his injury treated.

456
00:29:11,370 --> 00:29:14,783
Many players are poor,
and come from single parent households.

457
00:29:14,783 --> 00:29:20,069
Even so, monetary transactions
are a violation of the rules.

458
00:29:23,006 --> 00:29:24,324
Yes, I am aware.

459
00:29:30,359 --> 00:29:35,382
May I ask about the 2020 Draft?

460
00:29:36,244 --> 00:29:37,694
Pardon?

461
00:29:40,155 --> 00:29:45,591
Why was Satozaki your first round pick?

462
00:29:52,704 --> 00:29:54,381
Six years ago,

463
00:29:55,102 --> 00:29:57,984
I was scouting Gifu Daini High School,

464
00:29:57,984 --> 00:30:00,893
an obscure team that made it
to the prefectural finals.

465
00:30:04,232 --> 00:30:07,275
But the tournament was canceled due to COVID.

466
00:30:08,394 --> 00:30:12,472
I couldn't give up.

467
00:30:12,472 --> 00:30:14,391
I went to see them.

468
00:30:17,072 --> 00:30:20,676
The players weren't discouraged.

469
00:30:20,676 --> 00:30:22,699
<i>They were practicing.</i>

470
00:30:22,699 --> 00:30:26,518
With Koshien unfortunately canceled,

471
00:30:26,518 --> 00:30:32,024
I now realize we can never take
our games of baseball for granted.

472
00:30:34,053 --> 00:30:35,954
It's an odd feeling, really.

473
00:30:39,927 --> 00:30:42,444
But I will continue to play baseball,

474
00:30:42,444 --> 00:30:46,788
with this thought in my heart.

475
00:30:55,280 --> 00:30:59,334
I knew his humility
and passion for baseball...

476
00:31:00,102 --> 00:31:03,466
would surely bear fruit in the pros.

477
00:31:03,466 --> 00:31:07,773
That's why I went against
the Scouting Director's objections,

478
00:31:07,773 --> 00:31:13,193
and had the team draft him first.

479
00:31:13,193 --> 00:31:15,685
He was released after only three years.

480
00:31:15,685 --> 00:31:16,965
If he hadn't been injured...

481
00:31:16,965 --> 00:31:18,935
Being too soft-hearted...

482
00:31:19,751 --> 00:31:22,166
never benefits the team.

483
00:31:24,120 --> 00:31:25,570
Indeed.

484
00:31:26,481 --> 00:31:28,915
I admit I was wrong.

485
00:31:33,388 --> 00:31:35,722
My father was a huge baseball fan,

486
00:31:36,931 --> 00:31:39,575
and it was his dream for me to go pro.

487
00:31:41,232 --> 00:31:43,763
So, from the signing bonus...

488
00:31:45,403 --> 00:31:49,599
I thought it would be a one-time thing,
but he still demands a cut.

489
00:31:57,038 --> 00:32:01,598
What brought you to that field today?

490
00:32:06,631 --> 00:32:11,711
There's a pitcher at that university
who pitched well as a reliever

491
00:32:11,711 --> 00:32:14,082
even as a freshman.

492
00:32:14,082 --> 00:32:17,262
I came to check on his status.

493
00:32:17,262 --> 00:32:21,027
Are you preparing for the upcoming draft?

494
00:32:21,027 --> 00:32:22,621
Yes.

495
00:32:22,621 --> 00:32:25,029
A right-handed sidearm pitcher is valuable.

496
00:32:28,138 --> 00:32:33,179
His throws are speedy,
but his control is unstable.

497
00:32:34,935 --> 00:32:38,101
It might take time for him
to succeed as a pro.

498
00:32:40,933 --> 00:32:45,023
Our team currently needs players
who can show results, now.

499
00:32:47,284 --> 00:32:49,760
I believe it's best we pass on drafting him.

500
00:32:59,840 --> 00:33:08,510
[Scouting Director]

501
00:33:14,725 --> 00:33:15,804
What?

502
00:33:15,804 --> 00:33:17,432
What's wrong?

503
00:33:18,658 --> 00:33:22,521
What would you do, if I did something
to tarnish the team's name?

504
00:33:22,521 --> 00:33:25,772
Huh? Something, like what?

505
00:33:25,772 --> 00:33:28,068
Like taking bribes from a player.

506
00:33:28,068 --> 00:33:29,444
Holy cow, a bribe?

507
00:33:29,444 --> 00:33:31,488
How much did you get?

508
00:33:31,488 --> 00:33:32,823
- It was a hypothetical!
- Ow!

509
00:33:32,823 --> 00:33:35,562
Can you stop hitting me
for every little thing?

510
00:33:35,562 --> 00:33:37,960
But what would you do if it were true?

511
00:33:40,994 --> 00:33:45,143
I would trust your choice, ma'am.

512
00:33:46,212 --> 00:33:47,435
Why?

513
00:33:47,435 --> 00:33:50,229
Because I know you, Prez.

514
00:33:50,229 --> 00:33:52,216
I haven't been at your side for nothing.

515
00:33:54,569 --> 00:33:56,710
Don't trust me too much.

516
00:33:56,710 --> 00:33:58,807
If you're ever suspicious, doubt me.

517
00:33:58,807 --> 00:34:01,951
Believe, only after seeing the truth
for yourself.

518
00:34:01,951 --> 00:34:03,429
Am I clear?

519
00:34:04,367 --> 00:34:06,793
Sorry, I don't really get it.

520
00:34:13,918 --> 00:34:17,441
How can he be out, when drafts are coming up?

521
00:34:22,573 --> 00:34:25,369
Hello? Where are you right now?

522
00:34:25,369 --> 00:34:27,061
<i>I'm in Korea.</i>

523
00:34:27,061 --> 00:34:28,853
Korea?

524
00:34:29,506 --> 00:34:32,223
<i>I believe you called earlier?</i>

525
00:34:32,223 --> 00:34:35,609
I have a report regarding Mr. Kurokawa.

526
00:34:35,609 --> 00:34:39,343
<i>First, I'd like to ask you for a favor.</i>

527
00:34:39,343 --> 00:34:41,141
Sorry, a favor?

528
00:34:41,141 --> 00:34:44,176
I'm the one who's been trying to call you...

529
00:34:45,446 --> 00:34:48,496
[2026 Draft]

530
00:34:49,920 --> 00:34:51,030
[2026 Draft]

531
00:34:55,600 --> 00:34:59,900
[2026 Draft]

532
00:35:10,632 --> 00:35:14,313
This year's a bad crop,
so let's call it at round three,

533
00:35:14,313 --> 00:35:15,915
and head out for drinks.

534
00:35:15,915 --> 00:35:17,286
Excellent idea, sir.

535
00:35:17,286 --> 00:35:18,861
Let's get this over with.

536
00:35:18,861 --> 00:35:20,941
I'll go ahead and make a reservation.

537
00:35:20,941 --> 00:35:22,892
You're a bit too eager, aren't you?

538
00:35:22,892 --> 00:35:25,484
- Sorry, sorry.
- Bars aren't even open yet.

539
00:35:25,484 --> 00:35:26,864
I got ahead of myself.

540
00:35:26,864 --> 00:35:29,988
How about we first decide
between meat or fish?

541
00:35:29,988 --> 00:35:32,320
I'll take a vote.

542
00:35:33,049 --> 00:35:35,953
Prez, where have you been?

543
00:35:37,365 --> 00:35:39,035
What?

544
00:35:40,061 --> 00:35:41,576
What's wrong?

545
00:35:42,540 --> 00:35:44,695
There's something I'd like to discuss.

546
00:35:45,843 --> 00:35:50,057
If it's about changing a pick,
you're too late.

547
00:35:51,005 --> 00:35:53,053
Scouting Director Kurokawa.

548
00:35:56,747 --> 00:35:59,552
You are suspected of scouting bribery.

549
00:35:59,552 --> 00:36:00,928
Huh?

550
00:36:02,364 --> 00:36:03,931
You.

551
00:36:05,076 --> 00:36:06,766
What are you talking about?

552
00:36:06,766 --> 00:36:08,961
That's right, what are you talking about?

553
00:36:08,961 --> 00:36:11,273
Acting like a detective or something.

554
00:36:11,273 --> 00:36:13,709
Since 2020, the Dreams have scouted

555
00:36:13,709 --> 00:36:18,722
a total of 24 high school students
under your direction.

556
00:36:19,631 --> 00:36:27,356
<i>Among them, 12 students were drafted
from Seitoku Sports,</i>

557
00:36:27,356 --> 00:36:30,141
<i>Toei Tech, and Tomohama Academy.</i>

558
00:36:30,808 --> 00:36:33,090
Half of our 24 were from these three schools.

559
00:36:33,090 --> 00:36:35,846
Yeah. And what of it?

560
00:36:36,690 --> 00:36:40,232
The coach of Seitoku Sports
was your upperclassman.

561
00:36:40,232 --> 00:36:42,303
Yeah, from high school.

562
00:36:42,303 --> 00:36:43,839
And the coach of Toei Tech?

563
00:36:43,839 --> 00:36:45,543
Was an upperclassman in college.

564
00:36:45,543 --> 00:36:48,006
Is there a problem with that?

565
00:36:48,006 --> 00:36:51,812
What about the coach from Tomohama Academy?

566
00:36:51,812 --> 00:36:55,074
How am I connected to him?

567
00:36:56,199 --> 00:36:57,632
Answer me.

568
00:37:00,908 --> 00:37:03,007
The mountaineering club.

569
00:37:05,677 --> 00:37:07,871
<i>You're still around?</i>

570
00:37:07,871 --> 00:37:08,775
<i>Good work.</i>

571
00:37:08,775 --> 00:37:10,955
[Mountaineering Club 8th Anniversary]

572
00:37:22,500 --> 00:37:24,459
Bingo. You got it.

573
00:37:24,459 --> 00:37:27,072
I still don't see the issue here.

574
00:37:27,072 --> 00:37:30,393
We're close, so I get insider intel.

575
00:37:30,393 --> 00:37:32,025
It's inevitable I'll pick from their schools.

576
00:37:32,025 --> 00:37:36,184
Only one player you received intel about
has performed well.

577
00:37:36,184 --> 00:37:38,818
The others are late bloomers.

578
00:37:38,818 --> 00:37:40,120
Give them a few years.

579
00:37:40,120 --> 00:37:42,929
The Dreams need athletes
who can make plays, now.

580
00:37:42,929 --> 00:37:45,002
The team must have told you this already.

581
00:37:45,002 --> 00:37:49,435
Fine, call me incompetent, why don't you?

582
00:37:49,435 --> 00:37:51,995
Yeah, let's go with that.

583
00:37:54,082 --> 00:37:56,619
Didn't you make an under-the-table deal?

584
00:37:57,523 --> 00:37:59,146
Hey.

585
00:38:00,313 --> 00:38:02,312
Don't test me, Makita!

586
00:38:02,312 --> 00:38:05,181
Where's the evidence, huh?

587
00:38:05,181 --> 00:38:08,005
If you've got evidence, show it here!

588
00:38:14,329 --> 00:38:16,853
Accusing me with nothing to show?

589
00:38:16,853 --> 00:38:19,726
What's wrong with you?

590
00:38:20,994 --> 00:38:23,792
He's right, Prez.

591
00:38:27,690 --> 00:38:30,680
[I cannot go after all. I'm sorry.]

592
00:38:33,632 --> 00:38:35,391
I'm sorry.

593
00:38:43,607 --> 00:38:47,397
It's getting stuffy in here.

594
00:38:47,397 --> 00:38:50,772
What're you going to do about that, huh?

595
00:38:50,772 --> 00:38:53,324
I've never been so humiliated
in my entire career.

596
00:38:53,324 --> 00:38:57,949
Forget the draft.
You guys figure the rest of it out.

597
00:38:57,949 --> 00:38:59,322
No, no, no.

598
00:38:59,322 --> 00:39:01,650
Sir, we need you!

599
00:39:01,650 --> 00:39:04,774
Direct your complaints at that woman.

600
00:39:04,774 --> 00:39:06,195
President Makita.

601
00:39:06,195 --> 00:39:10,359
If this draft fails,
you'll be held responsible.

602
00:39:10,359 --> 00:39:13,105
You've upset our Scouting Chief.

603
00:39:13,105 --> 00:39:15,633
What're you going to do about that?

604
00:39:27,723 --> 00:39:30,595
This man has something to tell you all.

605
00:39:30,595 --> 00:39:32,973
Mr. Kurokawa, it's been a while.

606
00:39:36,378 --> 00:39:38,537
I'm Arihara, from the Vikings.

607
00:39:43,221 --> 00:39:44,652
In 2020,

608
00:39:44,652 --> 00:39:48,480
on the condition of a first-round pick,
I gave Mr. Kurokawa 5 million yen.

609
00:39:49,640 --> 00:39:51,766
Oh my god, it's true!

610
00:39:51,766 --> 00:39:54,829
However, the Vikings won
the luck of the draw.

611
00:39:54,829 --> 00:39:56,182
Watch it, Arihara.

612
00:39:56,182 --> 00:39:58,666
This is a recording of our deal.

613
00:39:58,666 --> 00:40:01,085
He clearly promises me a pick,

614
00:40:01,085 --> 00:40:03,911
and states I won't get my money back.

615
00:40:03,911 --> 00:40:07,156
Are you out of your mind?

616
00:40:07,156 --> 00:40:09,902
This is obviously nonsense.

617
00:40:09,902 --> 00:40:12,112
I don't mind playing this recording now.

618
00:40:13,193 --> 00:40:18,024
Your career will be over!

619
00:40:24,005 --> 00:40:25,934
Welcome.

620
00:40:32,191 --> 00:40:34,707
How do you know about our deal?

621
00:40:35,882 --> 00:40:37,950
The day after the draft,

622
00:40:37,950 --> 00:40:41,182
Mr. Kurokawa was seen
visiting your high school.

623
00:40:41,182 --> 00:40:43,503
It was captured on video.

624
00:40:43,503 --> 00:40:46,647
Why did Mr. Kurokawa come to see you?

625
00:40:48,602 --> 00:40:51,502
Wasn't it because he couldn't pick you?

626
00:40:52,634 --> 00:40:54,966
When you won Rookie of the Year,

627
00:40:54,966 --> 00:40:57,487
could you earnestly be proud
of your accomplishments?

628
00:41:00,510 --> 00:41:02,852
Are you telling me
to get it all off my chest?

629
00:41:02,852 --> 00:41:06,550
You can't turn over a new leaf
if you continue to hide your wrongdoings.

630
00:41:13,741 --> 00:41:17,261
Your brother also plays baseball
in high school, yes?

631
00:41:19,369 --> 00:41:21,666
Are you going to teach him your ways?

632
00:41:22,398 --> 00:41:24,710
This way of joining a team?

633
00:41:34,993 --> 00:41:37,156
Scouting Director Kurokawa.

634
00:41:38,365 --> 00:41:41,592
Please return the 5 million yen to Arihara.

635
00:41:44,031 --> 00:41:46,081
You...

636
00:41:47,917 --> 00:41:49,477
are fired.

637
00:41:49,477 --> 00:41:52,287
- What?
- Fired?

638
00:41:52,287 --> 00:41:54,456
This is tyranny! Tyranny!

639
00:41:54,456 --> 00:41:55,836
Absolute tyranny, I say!

640
00:41:55,836 --> 00:41:59,273
He's right. Firing the Scouting Director
right before the draft...

641
00:41:59,273 --> 00:42:01,096
It's simply going too far!

642
00:42:07,094 --> 00:42:09,471
Osanai.

643
00:42:09,471 --> 00:42:11,411
You.

644
00:42:11,411 --> 00:42:13,917
Where have you been all this time?

645
00:42:14,550 --> 00:42:16,334
I'm appointing Mr. Osanai...

646
00:42:17,203 --> 00:42:19,715
as the new Scouting Director.

647
00:42:25,090 --> 00:42:27,040
[2026 Professional Baseball Draft]

648
00:42:28,816 --> 00:42:32,403
Ladies and gentlemen,
thank you for waiting.

649
00:42:32,403 --> 00:42:36,316
The 2026 Professional Baseball Draft
shall now commence.

650
00:42:36,316 --> 00:42:39,035
Please welcome in the 12 teams.

651
00:42:49,753 --> 00:42:52,556
The Toyohashi Yaoshima Dreams!

652
00:43:04,709 --> 00:43:06,879
The Chiba Ocean Waves!

653
00:43:16,049 --> 00:43:18,990
The Yokohama Mardline Vikings!

654
00:43:23,252 --> 00:43:25,989
The Tokyo Smile Pelicans!

655
00:43:28,484 --> 00:43:29,511
Kansai Electric Railway Octopathy!

656
00:43:29,511 --> 00:43:33,000
Please pick many players who will be popular!

657
00:43:33,000 --> 00:43:34,116
Please!

658
00:43:34,116 --> 00:43:36,166
Let's all send them our prayers!

659
00:43:37,548 --> 00:43:40,208
Oh, no, what should I do?

660
00:43:40,208 --> 00:43:42,589
Why are you the most nervous one here?

661
00:43:42,589 --> 00:43:45,616
- Sit down.
- I know, I know it's weird.

662
00:43:45,616 --> 00:43:48,062
But I have the right to be nervous too.

663
00:43:48,062 --> 00:43:51,716
Stop it, your nerves are rubbing off on me.

664
00:43:51,716 --> 00:43:53,995
How about we take deep breaths together?

665
00:43:59,273 --> 00:44:03,161
You shoot down all my suggestions.

666
00:44:03,161 --> 00:44:05,831
Mind if I join your breathing exercises?

667
00:44:05,831 --> 00:44:07,189
Sure.

668
00:44:09,609 --> 00:44:11,167
Please sit.

669
00:44:11,167 --> 00:44:12,954
- No standing?
- All teams have been seated.

670
00:44:12,954 --> 00:44:13,935
It's starting.

671
00:44:13,935 --> 00:44:17,243
We will now read out the first-round picks.

672
00:44:18,199 --> 00:44:20,963
First Draft Pick.

673
00:44:20,963 --> 00:44:23,196
Toyohashi Yaoshima.

674
00:44:23,891 --> 00:44:25,724
Yuki Tanaka.

675
00:44:25,724 --> 00:44:28,744
Pitcher, Midoriyama University.

676
00:44:36,502 --> 00:44:38,274
First Draft Pick.

677
00:44:38,274 --> 00:44:41,064
Yokohama Mardline.

678
00:44:41,064 --> 00:44:42,760
Yuki Tanaka.

679
00:44:42,760 --> 00:44:45,967
Pitcher, Midoriyama Gakuen University.

680
00:44:48,321 --> 00:44:50,957
Tokyo Smile.

681
00:44:50,957 --> 00:44:52,820
Yuki Tanaka.

682
00:44:52,820 --> 00:44:56,004
Pitcher, Midoriyama University.

683
00:45:01,767 --> 00:45:06,352
Wow, six teams have picked Tanaka.

684
00:45:06,352 --> 00:45:10,321
Don't make a fuss.
The GM will draw us Tanaka.

685
00:45:10,321 --> 00:45:12,150
We're counting on you, GM!

686
00:45:14,277 --> 00:45:16,825
Maintaining composure is key.

687
00:45:17,760 --> 00:45:22,677
Representatives from the six teams,
please come to the stage.

688
00:45:25,820 --> 00:45:27,832
The GM will surely make it happen.

689
00:45:27,832 --> 00:45:29,909
We're counting on you.

690
00:45:29,909 --> 00:45:31,765
Please, GM!

691
00:45:39,784 --> 00:45:41,467
Which one?

692
00:45:42,978 --> 00:45:46,421
Which hand will you use to draw?
Right or left?

693
00:45:48,055 --> 00:45:53,635
They say it's good to use
your non-dominant hand.

694
00:45:53,635 --> 00:45:55,413
I see.

695
00:45:55,413 --> 00:45:57,278
Please.

696
00:45:57,278 --> 00:45:59,775
Please come up to the stage.

697
00:46:18,937 --> 00:46:21,722
Toyohashi Yaoshima.

698
00:46:57,391 --> 00:47:00,370
Yokohama Mardline.

699
00:47:20,274 --> 00:47:23,449
Please open your envelopes.

700
00:47:25,248 --> 00:47:27,208
Please, please, please.

701
00:47:27,208 --> 00:47:30,249
Please, please, please.

702
00:47:38,767 --> 00:47:39,660
Yes!

703
00:47:39,660 --> 00:47:41,358
Alright!

704
00:47:41,358 --> 00:47:44,899
Yuki Tanaka will be signed
to the Tokyo Smiles.

705
00:47:44,899 --> 00:47:46,607
- Huh?
- Why?

706
00:47:46,607 --> 00:47:48,385
Are you serious?

707
00:47:51,989 --> 00:47:54,102
Aw...

708
00:47:54,102 --> 00:47:56,957
Why is he so calm? We lost our first pick!

709
00:47:56,957 --> 00:47:59,512
Boo! Boo! Boo!

710
00:48:02,123 --> 00:48:04,473
What's with that attitude?

711
00:48:04,473 --> 00:48:06,519
I've always had bad luck with lotteries.

712
00:48:06,519 --> 00:48:07,730
Huh?

713
00:48:07,730 --> 00:48:10,941
Why aren't you more disappointed?

714
00:48:11,584 --> 00:48:13,410
Should I be?

715
00:48:13,410 --> 00:48:14,698
Look, here.

716
00:48:14,698 --> 00:48:15,727
- Now, now, now.
- Prez.

717
00:48:15,727 --> 00:48:18,175
Maybe not now.

718
00:48:18,175 --> 00:48:19,964
Ow! Why me?

719
00:48:19,964 --> 00:48:22,061
I needed an outlet.

720
00:48:22,061 --> 00:48:24,006
Ow! What? Why me?

721
00:48:24,006 --> 00:48:25,656
I needed an outlet, too.

722
00:48:25,656 --> 00:48:28,191
There are still plenty of good players.

723
00:48:29,236 --> 00:48:30,719
GM.

724
00:48:38,498 --> 00:48:40,948
First Round Pick.

725
00:48:40,948 --> 00:48:43,916
Toyohashi Yaoshima.

726
00:48:43,916 --> 00:48:45,484
Lim Min Jong.

727
00:48:45,484 --> 00:48:48,495
Pitcher, Busan University
of Information Sciences.

728
00:48:54,070 --> 00:48:56,952
Are there any other players
you're interested in?

729
00:48:56,952 --> 00:48:58,163
Huh?

730
00:48:59,104 --> 00:49:01,083
If not, that's fine.

731
00:49:02,006 --> 00:49:03,919
Yes! There are!

732
00:49:05,733 --> 00:49:07,648
Please take a look at this.

733
00:49:07,648 --> 00:49:10,976
He was the ace of Gifu High at the time.

734
00:49:14,549 --> 00:49:16,163
Lim Min Jong?

735
00:49:16,163 --> 00:49:17,243
Yes.

736
00:49:17,243 --> 00:49:19,346
After the Koshien was canceled in 2020,

737
00:49:19,346 --> 00:49:23,615
he returned to Korea
without ever showcasing his skills.

738
00:49:23,615 --> 00:49:26,550
Can he be chosen in the Japanese draft?

739
00:49:26,550 --> 00:49:31,458
Since he graduated
from a Japanese high school, yes.

740
00:49:38,220 --> 00:49:41,204
They got me.

741
00:49:41,204 --> 00:49:44,133
So they had their eyes on Lim.

742
00:49:44,133 --> 00:49:45,983
And he was their first-round pick.

743
00:49:45,983 --> 00:49:46,838
Korea?

744
00:49:46,838 --> 00:49:48,938
- Know him?
- Can't say I do.

745
00:49:50,787 --> 00:49:53,568
Trying to show off, eh?

746
00:49:53,568 --> 00:49:56,730
That's what a weak team would do.

747
00:50:03,810 --> 00:50:10,119
Lim Min Jong has been confirmed
as the pick for Toyohashi Yaoshima.

748
00:50:10,119 --> 00:50:12,010
Alright!

749
00:50:20,164 --> 00:50:23,149
Ow! Why me again?

750
00:50:23,149 --> 00:50:24,783
Ow!

751
00:50:33,275 --> 00:50:35,860
[Dreams' surprise pick of Lim Min Jong]

752
00:50:35,860 --> 00:50:38,335
[The Birth of a New Ace]

753
00:50:38,335 --> 00:50:41,025
[Lim Min Jong is the Dreams' first pick]

754
00:51:03,012 --> 00:51:08,243
15 years ago,
you faced off against the Vikings.

755
00:51:10,084 --> 00:51:13,206
It was the bottom of the 9th,
two outs, bases loaded.

756
00:51:14,083 --> 00:51:16,710
You were at bat, sir.

757
00:51:20,509 --> 00:51:27,137
You said the umpire's dead ball
was called on a foul.

758
00:51:29,046 --> 00:51:31,391
You said the ball grazed your bat.

759
00:51:34,899 --> 00:51:37,522
Even though we lost the game,

760
00:51:39,034 --> 00:51:41,051
you were absolutely amazing, sir.

761
00:51:43,529 --> 00:51:48,075
Back then, I was still young.

762
00:51:50,379 --> 00:51:52,746
You were the embodiment of justice, sir.

763
00:52:05,604 --> 00:52:07,452
Good work.

764
00:52:11,599 --> 00:52:16,008
What kind of person was he?

765
00:52:19,288 --> 00:52:22,342
He had his own idea of the perfect swing,

766
00:52:23,036 --> 00:52:26,988
and was a sociable person
who could befriend anyone.

767
00:52:28,487 --> 00:52:32,536
Everyone recognized his eye
for evaluating batters.

768
00:52:35,719 --> 00:52:39,742
But he strayed from that path.

769
00:52:41,732 --> 00:52:44,480
To quote someone I know.

770
00:52:44,480 --> 00:52:48,542
"People have two sides to them."

771
00:52:48,542 --> 00:52:50,612
"Look at them both."

772
00:52:53,550 --> 00:52:55,256
Like you do.

773
00:52:58,668 --> 00:52:59,938
Huh?

774
00:53:04,202 --> 00:53:06,925
Was that a compliment?

775
00:53:06,925 --> 00:53:10,140
You just complimented me, right? Right?

776
00:53:10,140 --> 00:53:14,775
Well, you're right.
I do see the good and bad in people.

777
00:53:14,775 --> 00:53:16,515
It's a skill of mine.

778
00:53:20,064 --> 00:53:26,706
Do you recall what I said
after Kudo was traded away?

779
00:53:31,685 --> 00:53:36,582
Why sow unnecessary seeds
when the team has no tomorrow?

780
00:53:38,884 --> 00:53:41,154
I'm simply following my resume.

781
00:53:42,272 --> 00:53:44,807
I asked for a disbandment.

782
00:53:45,969 --> 00:53:50,021
Disbanding wasn't the only thing
on my resume.

783
00:53:52,993 --> 00:53:56,186
Victory first.

784
00:53:59,617 --> 00:54:01,358
Then disbandment.

785
00:54:05,053 --> 00:54:08,690
Do you really think this team can win?

786
00:54:11,487 --> 00:54:15,221
You only acquired Sawada.

787
00:54:17,667 --> 00:54:19,584
Sir.

788
00:54:21,357 --> 00:54:23,071
I will meet your expectations.

